              <p>
                If <m>a+2=5</m>, then <m>8\lt 5</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                If <m>5\lt 8</m>, then <m>a+2=5</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li xml:id="exer_sec11-5">
        <p>
          Let <m>P</m> be the statement
          <q>Student X passed every assignment in Calculus I,</q>
          and let <m>Q</m> be the statement
          <q>Student X received a grade of C or better in Calculus I.</q>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                What does it mean for <m>P</m> to be true?
                What does it mean for <m>Q</m> to be true?
              </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="exer_conditionalb">
              <p>
                Suppose that Student X passed every assignment in Calculus I and received a grade of B<m>-</m>,
