          <ul>
            \item <em>Theorem</em>. If <m>f</m> is a quadratic function of the form <m>f\left( x \right) = ax^2 + bx + c</m> and <m>a \lt 0</m>, then the function <m>f</m> has a maximum value when <m>x = \dfrac{{ - b}}{{2a}}</m>.
          </ul>
        </p>
        Using <em>only</em> this theorem, what can be concluded about the functions given by the following formulas?
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>g\left( x \right) = - 8x^2 + 5x - 2</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>h\left( x \right) = - \dfrac{1}{3}x^2 + 3x</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>k\left( x \right) = 8x^2 - 5x - 7</m>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              <m>j\left( x \right) = - \dfrac{{71}}{{99}}x^2 + 210</m>
